                <h3>WEEK SIX - Assignment 1 Progression </h3>
                <p>In this week’s lecture we did the presentation for assignment one and introduced the tasks we need to in the next assignment. 

                    Assignment one reflection: To sum up, through the user persona, user empathy map, Vinn diagram, user flow and customer journey map. I have eventually built the foundations of a website that can help people with autism to achieve their goals and get social support. The website will provide online courses and tutorials to self-educate on the topics they are interested in. They can also use this website to find potential employers or have their resumes reviewed by professionals. </p>

            <h3>WEEK SEVEN - Colour Theory + UX Laws</h3>
            <p>First lecture after mid-trimester break, we learnt why it is important to create a good visual hierarchy by having the good colour contract. To continue, we learnt how to create good colour contract by putting warm and cold colours together or increasing the saturation and lightness of coulours. 

                After we did some practice on how to create layout by using CSS grids and get individual helps for the assignment two. Here are my Lo-fi hand-drawnm phone wireframes and website wireframes I have created during break. </p>
                <img src="lo-fi wireframe phone.png">
                <img src="lo-fi wireframe website.png">
            <h3>WEEK EIGHT - Typography + CSS Grids part 2 (responsive design) </h3>
            <p>In this week’s lecture we talked about why typography is so important for website design and how to choose the right website typeface by considering the line spacing, colours, visual hierarchy, font type and size. 

                Then we did a draft presentation for project 2 and got feedback from tutors.  
                
                Here is the feedback I got today:
                <ul>
                    <li>Think about the color palates. The pink color with black color font does not match and does not have a good contract. </li>
                    <li>About the personality test. Make sure all the answers are easy toread and click on. The layout needs to be adjusted and refined. Take off the “skip all the questions” option. </li>
                    <li>Add a personalization setting function for users to create their preferences for the most comfortable way to interact with the website</li>
                  </ul> </p>
                <img src="hi-fi website phone.png">
                <img src="hi-fi wireframe website.png">
                <h3>WEEK NINE - Assignment 2-1 Progress + Editor X Basics </h3>
                <p>This week we did presentations for assignment 2-1. Here is the reflection I had for this assignment: If I could do this assignment again, I would join communities like IHC Volunteer to work with my users and get to know them in real life instead of through articles or other people's words. I would also consider the design system at the beginning so I can slowly build up the system as I develop my website instead of leaving them at the lastminute. But overall, I am happy with my outcomes as this is my first time designing a website. 
               
                    After the presentation, we had an introduction about what we need to do for assignment 2-2. </p>
